⸻

Known failure cases

This version will fail often across the wider internet.

Fails or struggles when:
	•	both users are behind strict NAT
	•	IP changed and no new path is known
	•	mobile carrier blocks inbound
	•	MAC randomization hides local identity
	•	both users are offline at different times with no overlap
	•	no relay exists and no successful prior route exists

That is not a bug in the design. It is the natural limit of "pure remembered-address P2P with no hub."

⸻

What makes this still useful

v0.1 can still be good for:
	•	friends on same LAN / same building / same village network
	•	households
	•	family compounds
	•	maker communities
	•	disaster fallback within local area
	•	occasional direct contact when public IP remains reachable
	•	proving the Beast protocol and identity model

It is a solid seed.

⸻

Clean v0.1 principle

Beast Comms v0.1 does not promise universal reachability. It promises direct encrypted delivery whenever a known path exists, and honest queueing when it does not.

That is the right first promise.

